The White House will be hosting a convening on Women and the Criminal Justice System. The event aims to bring together justice-involved women and girls, family members of incarcerated individuals, women in law enforcement, and other advocates for a more equitable and effective justice system. The discussion will focus on improving women's access to justice in the community, courtroom, and cell block. Participants include U.S. Attorney General Loretta E. Lynch, Senior Advisor to the President Valerie Jarrett, and various other professionals in the field. The event will be live-streamed and can be accessed at obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/live.